==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: morel
<hw>mor"el</hw> <pr>(m⟦ocr⟧r"⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>moril</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An edible fungus
(<spn>Morchella esculenta</spn>), the upper part of which is covered
with a reticulated and pitted hymenium. It is used as food, and for
flavoring sauces.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>moril</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>morel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: morel
<hw>mor"el</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>morelle</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Nightshade; -- so called from its
blackish purple berries.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>morelle</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of cherry. See <er>Morello</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Great morel</b></col>, <cd>the deadly nightshade.</cd> --
<col><b>Petty morel</b></col>, <cd>the black nightshade. See
<er>Nightshade</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>moreland</ent>⟦br⟧
